ty decision was based on the fact that the reporter found two very similar vulnerabilities (a pattern issue, \u003ca href=\"/reports/181803\"\u003e#181803\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"/reports/181826\"\u003e#181826\u003c/a\u003e) -  the bounty was bundled and then split amongst both reports.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"id":3068,"category":"researcher","content":"I do not agree that this is a very similar vulnerabilities ( #181803 and #181826 ). \nThus we can say that all SQL injection similar to each other.\nBut never mind, thanks for bounty.","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003eI do not agree that this is a very similar vulnerabilities ( \u003ca href=\"/reports/181803\"\u003e#181803\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"/reports/181826\"\u003e#181826\u003c/a\u003e ). \u003cbr\u003e\nThus we can say that all SQL injection similar to each other.\u003cbr\u003e\nBut never mind, thanks for bounty.\u003c/p\u003e\n"}]}